messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /printshops/{id}/pricetable/papers

- all HTTP methods accepted: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: true
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The editPaperItem handler in PriceTableController is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/papers", method = RequestMethod.PUT) so PUT is explicitly supported for that path.
- The same path has another method addNewPaperItem annotated with @RequestMapping(..., method = RequestMethod.POST) so POST is explicitly supported as well.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would change the path prefix, so the full path is exactly the method-level value: /printshops/{id}/pricetable/papers.
- No handler in the provided controller is declared for GET, HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, DELETE, or PATCH on that path, therefore (per the code) those methods are not accepted. (Security annotations like @Secured affect authorization but do not change which HTTP methods are mapped.)
